            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I wrote by the ships mail; so as I have no bill of loading I hope Mr Bentham will kindly <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">secure the box at once after the arrival of the Dover Castle</hi>
               </seg>, as the agents &amp; owners of the ship would not be responsible for it.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr Bentham will find the long series of forms of <name key="Rutaceae">Rutaceae</name> instructive in the highest degree.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have relinquished my seat in the Council of our Royal Society, where I was Office bearer ever since 1854, when I aided in the formation of the Society; also my seat in the Explor. Committee, merely to gain more time &amp; taking a more prominent share in Benthams work. I would like to work up some orders myself, as far as my material goes, which could then easily be completed by Mr Bentham. Perhaps I take up <name key="Myrtaceae">Myrtaceae</name> &amp; <name key="Rhamnaceae">Rhamnaceae</name>. I might also work up the <name key="Sapindaceae">Sapindaceae</name> &amp; some more orders of <name key="Thalamiflorae">Thalamiflorae</name>, if I had Dr Hookers genera plantarum<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83).</p>
               </note> in time. I would be so glad, if I could obtain in a similar way proofsheets, as Dr Hance received the Hong Kong flora, both of the genera plantarum &amp; the Austral. flora.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>There will be 3 or 4 cases yet of <name key="Thalamiflorae">Thalamiflorae</name> to send, and then it will be perhaps necessary to send the supplemental collections, which are rapidly accumulating. Whether I should work out these here (after receipt of proof sheets) or whether I should send them finally also, will be for Mr Benthams consideration.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The bountiful supply of herbaceous seeds was brought by Mr G. M'Leay himself &amp; indeed I am thankful for so large a variety of species new to our Garden. The Nile papyrus seems to have died on its way to Sydney but I am promised to receive part of the other waterplants from Mr W. S M'Leay.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letters not found.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Would you kindly give me your opinion on the supposed new Bixineous genus enclosed. That the genus <name key="Sturtia">Sturtia</name> is only a subgenus of <name key="Gossypium">Gossypium</name> you will observe by the enclosed fragments.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir Ch. Nicholson went home and passed through Melbourne, without my having had an opportunity to bid him farewell. I am usually so absorbed in my departmental work, that I do not learn of any visits of distinguished men.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The living plants per Suffolk and by overland mail (the latter under Mr M'Leays care) I hope will reach you in safety.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
